required.hint:
Pricing model. Accepts shorthand strings for simple cases OR a full object for committed pricing.

Shorthand (On-Demand/Spot only): "ondemand", "spot"

Full object (required for any committed/discounted pricing):
- EC2 Instance Savings Plans: {"model":"instanceSavings","term":"1 Year","upfrontPayment":"None"}
- Compute Savings Plans: {"model":"computeSavings","term":"1 Year","upfrontPayment":"None"}
- Standard Reserved Instances (dedicated tenancy only): {"model":"standard","term":"1 Year","upfrontPayment":"None"}
- Convertible Reserved Instances (dedicated tenancy only): {"model":"convertible","term":"1 Year","upfrontPayment":"None"}

Valid term values: "1 Year", "3 Year" (exact case, full words)
Valid upfrontPayment values: "None", "Partial", "All" (exact case)

CRITICAL: Do NOT use shorthand "reserved" or "instanceSavings" for committed pricing — these may silently fall back to On-Demand or produce $0 costs. Always use the full object format for any non-OnDemand, non-Spot pricing. EstimateBuilder normalizes via lib/ec2.js.
